    <h3><ol>
        <li>Vedic Studies - Rigveda, Samaveda, Yajurveda, Atharvaveda</li>
        <li>Philosophy - Upanishads, Vedanta, and Dharma Shastras</li>
        <li>Sanskrit Language and Grammar</li>
        <li>Mathematics - Arithmetic, Geometry, and Algebra</li>
        <li>Logic and Debate - Nyaya and Tarka (Logic and reasoning)</li>
        <li>Sciences - Ayurveda (medicine), Jyotisha (astronomy/astrology)</li>
        <li>Ethics and Morality - Understanding Dharma (righteous living)</li>
        <li>Yoga and Meditation</li>
        <li>Physical Training - Archery, swordsmanship, and self-defense</li>
        <li>Music and Arts - Classical music, dance, and fine arts</li>
        <li>Economics and Governance - Arthashastra, political science, and administration</li>
        <li>Environmental Studies - Understanding nature and seasons</li>
        <li>Agriculture and Farming - Knowledge of crops and seasons</li>
        <li>Self-Discipline and Personal Development</li>
        <li>Spiritual Practices - Chanting, rituals, and worship</li>
    </ol></h3>
